{
  "stem": "20089.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But what happened, and I heard that subsequently, was that one person would then go-- the person that had signed then would go to the end of the queue, and make up a fictitious name.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So that instead of having a supply, say for 500, there was supplies given for a thousand.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Because everybody had-- had signed their names twice, or other names twice.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there-- there weren't really many family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were some families.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But as I said, most of the children were under the Madrichim.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the whole idea of these-- these groups, was that the Jewish agency wanted to take them out of the camp through to Marseilles, and then on to-- Haifa, and illegally into Palestine.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at the time, of course, British-- the British were in control of Palestine, and the number of immigrants that were allowed into Palestine was-- there was a limited number every month.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And what the Jewish agency often did was take them through to-- to Haifa, and get them in illegally, and perhaps one remembers which was a ship that was stopped by the British.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A lot of the children on originally came from Rosenheim.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were taken from Rosenheim through to ship.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And ship was stopped, if you remember.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the British sent them back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they went back to-- I think the British there-- it was under the British.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But the work of the Jewish agency was really to get as many people into Palestine as possible.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because I think that they were hoping that Palestine would eventually become the state for the Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But at that-- in 1946, '47, it was still a dream, not a reality.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What you mean by transportation services, the illegal or the legal?",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
